This paper is about a website fingerprinting technique that can be used to infer which web page a client is browsing through encrypted or anonymized network connections. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also uses random decision forests, which is a machine learning technique, making it relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of website fingerprinting defenses, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
